<TEXT>
photos of neptune taken by voyager 2 this 
week will be appearing on television sets in homes around the 
country during the flyby and for the price of a telephone call 
voyager enthusiasts will be listening to nasa news updates on the 
mission 
many cable television subscribers and people with satellite 
dishes will be watching closedcircuit nasa select television 
broadcasts of the voyager photos more than 3000 cable tv 
companies observatories universities and other institutions were 
invited to transmit nasa programming over public access channels or 
to audiences in planetariums or auditoriums 
the national aeronautics and space administration planned the 
broadcasts from 9 am to 11 pm pdt today through wednesday from 
9 am pdt probably through the night on aug 24 from 9 am to 11 
pm pdt aug 2528 and from 9 am to 1230 pm pdt aug 29 
viewers must check with their local cable tv companies to learn 
if the broadcasts will be carried in their city 
cable news network planned brief live reports at 2 pm 5 pm 7 
pm and 9 pm pdt starting today 
the special telephone line 900 5901234 will provide 
frequently updated recorded status reports on the voyager mission 
this line will carry live audio from the news conferences that were 
scheduled to start at 10 am pdt daily today through aug 29 the 
cost of calls to this line is 45 cents for the first minute and 35 
cents for each additional minute 
similar programs are available by calling 818 3544227 818 
3540409 or 818 3547292 special lines at jpl normal 
longdistance charges apply 
on its tv broadcasts nasa select will show voyager 2s 
photographs of neptune its moons and partial rings and also will 
carry live news conferences by voyager scientists there will be 
short hourly programs about voyager at neptune 
satellite dish owners throughout most of the united states may 
receive nasa select by tuning to ge satcom f2r transponder 13 71 
degrees west longitude 3960 megahertz vertical polarity 
satellite dish owners in alaska and hawaii should tune to aurora 
1 transponder 21 143 west longitude 4120 megahertz vertical 
polarity aurora 1 also may provide better reception than satcom f2r 
for west coast dish owners 
