what was once viewed as impossible has happened in poland 
for seven years people risked arrest for even showing the 
solidarity logo now members of parliament wear it on their lapels 
shoppers bear it on their tote bags and everyone sees it on a banner 
stretched across warsaws main square 
opposition activists jailed for daring to challenge to the 
government now are legislators all three of the men president 
