prospects for talks in south africa when he welcomes acting south 
african president fw de klerk to zambia on monday 
besides ending the emergency and lifting bans on antiapartheid 
groups and individual activists the harare summits conditions 
included the removal of all troops from south africas black 
townships releasing all political prisoners and ending political 
trials and executions and a government commitment to free political 
discussion 
only then could the government and its opponents discuss a 
ceasefire the formation of an interim government and a 
