impaired by staff shortages at the centers for disease control the 
general accounting office said monday 
the arm of cdc that handles education programs the center for 
prevention services requested additional staff four times in 1988 
said a report from gao the congressional investigative body 
but cdc was unable to provide the additional employees because 
