group who would be expected to have lower subsequent accident 
rates 
nevertheless it said there was suggestive evidence that the 
driver training course helped reduce accident risk 
we feel the results are quite suggestive and promising said 
ray peck director of research for the california department of 
motor vehicles 
drivers over age 65 are second only to those age 15 to 24 in 
traffic accidents and when the number of miles driven is taken into 
account the two groups are almost equal 
results of the california study were released here by the 
nations largest senior citizen organization the american 
association of retired persons 
aarp presidentelect robert maxwell said the study shows 
refresher courses are one way older drivers can remain safe 
drivers longer 
to lose the ability to drive often traps older people in their 
homes because of that we are dedicated to helping older drivers 
remain safe drivers 
the california study compared driving records for 40339 
graduates of the states mature driver improvement program with 
those of 75064 older drivers who did not take the course all were 
age 55 or above 
adjusting the results to factor out differences between the two 
groups the graduates had 16 percent fewer accidents involving death 
or injury and 157 percent fewer traffic convictions 
most of the participants in the california program took the 55 
alive course developed by aarp california drivers over age 55 who 
take an approved refresher course are eligible for reduced auto 
insurance premiums 
