investment ltd to try to take over bat 
the takeover of the british conglomerate would be the worlds 
second largest after the 2453 billion acquisition of rjr nabisco 
inc by kohlberg kravis roberts amp co 
hoylake has argued that bat shareholders would get far better 
value if bats assets were unbundled hoylake has said it would 
sell bats nontobacco businesses which include financial services 
retailing and paper 
