consisted of a package of securities of dubious value it 
asserted that even hoylake admitted it may be impossible to sell 
the debt instruments it is offering for bat stock 
the company said hoylakes proposal to acquire bat rests on a 
bewildering array of interlocking companies most of whom are 
resident in tax havens its vastly complex structure is designed to 
add an enormous amount of money to the already substantial fortunes 
of goldsmith rothschild and packer at the expense of the 
shareholders of bat 
